<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>No adverse health effects related to radiation were ever observed among people exposed to such high natural doses. This strongly suggests that the current radiation standards are excessively, and unnecessarily, restrictive.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'd rather live next to a nuclear power plant than a coal burning one any day.  The central coast in California has two power plants that are only about 10 miles apart and it never fails to amaze me how dirty and obstructive to the environment the fossil fuels burning plant is compared to the Diablo Canyon nuclear plant.  Not only do the giant smoke stacks on the fossil fuel plant marr the landscape it often makes a large area of the beach smell like rotten eggs from the sulfur it spews out.  The nuclear plant on the other hand isn't visible at all and the only reason you know it's there in the first place is because of the signs on the road.  And no doubt, the radioactivity being released from the coal plant is probably a lot higher than that being released from the nuclear plant because the nuke plant is designed to block radiation.  I think the only real danger from nuclear plants is in the waste and maybe the transportation of the fuel, I just don't buy the safety issues with the reactor itself being something worth losing sleep over.   Maybe a Cherynobyl reactor but not newer, Western designs.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 2/28/03 9:56:39 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#6F6F6F>- </font><a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace>NuclearSpace Message Board</a><font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1>Open Forum</a> <font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><a href="http://www.nuclearspace.com">NuclearSpace Home Page</a><font color=#6F6F6F> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.31b<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  